- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper deals with the representation of causal dependencies among events in Petri nets.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible because the paper discusses the construction of operational models for expressing causality in Petri nets, which could be relevant to software engineering.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is possible because the paper discusses the equivalence between coalgebras over a class of presheaves and History Dependent automata.
